"""Phase H — end-to-end verification of the cascade I/O migration.

The migration's terminal phase: a default-mode cascade run produces

  * ``output_raw/v_*.parquet`` (raw LP-variable trail)
  * ``output_processed/*`` (per ``--write-methods``)
  * ``manifest.json`` (auto-generated by ``_parquet_bundle.write_manifest``)

and NO cascade-internal CSVs in ``input/``, ``solve_data/``, or
``cross_solve/`` (modulo a documented set of out-of-scope writers — see
the ``_DOCUMENTED_OUT_OF_SCOPE`` whitelist below).  Adding ``--csv-dump``
reproduces the legacy CSV layout under ``solve_data/`` (and friends).

What this module asserts
------------------------

For each of two representative fixtures (``work_base`` single-solve and
``work_5weeks_invest_fullYear_dispatch_coal_wind`` two-solve cascade) we
exercise the cascade THREE ways and inspect the on-disk bundle:

* **default mode** — ``the in-memory cascade`` wraps the cascade
  exactly the way ``cmd_run_flextool.py:_run_native_solve`` does when
  the user does NOT pass ``--csv-dump``.

  Asserts:
    - ``output_raw/`` contains ``v_*.parquet`` (>= 1).
    - ``solve_data/`` either does not exist OR contains only files
      listed in ``_DOCUMENTED_OUT_OF_SCOPE`` (out-of-scope writers
      retained by earlier Phase E-d / E-e dispatches).
    - ``cross_solve/`` does not exist OR contains no ``*.csv`` (the
      cross-solve carriers ride in ``state.cross_solve_carriers`` per
      Phase E-d).
    - ``input/`` may exist with CSVs — the legacy ``write_input`` direct
      ``csv.writer`` writes were NOT gated in Phase E (out-of-scope as
      noted in commit ``09f3b363`` Phase E-c notes).
    - ``write_manifest`` produces ``manifest.json`` with the documented
      schema (version "1", ``generated_at`` ISO 8601, ``files`` list);
      every ``files[i].exists`` true entry maps to a real file under
      the bundle root.
    - Cascade's final objective is captured (used for parity check).

* **--csv-dump mode** — no ``the in-memory cascade`` wrap (CSV
  emission on, the legacy behaviour).  Asserts ``solve_data/`` contains
  the legacy CSV set (sample a handful of basenames), confirms manifest
  + raw parquets, and asserts objective matches the default-mode run
  within ``rel_tol=1e-6``.

* **legacy mode** — i.e. a disk-only orchestration path that bypasses
  the in-memory cascade.  Phase E retired this entry point; there is no
  longer a separate ``run_disk_only`` orchestration.  The test
  documents this with a ``pytest.skip``.

The multi-roll fixture under ``the in-memory cascade`` is currently
broken (Phase H surfaced the regression: ``input.py::_load_process_topology``
calls ``_read_p_flow_max``, ``_read_unitsize``, and ~30 other helpers
that use ``if not path.exists(): return None`` — these are NOT
seed-aware loaders, only the writer-side ``_emit_*`` modules were
seed-wired in Phase E-e).  The multi-roll csv-dump-mode case still
passes; we keep that gate.  Lifting the loader-side reads onto the seed
funnel is tracked as a follow-up — out of Phase H scope per the task
constraint "DON'T change production code unless precise fix".  The
single-roll csv-disabled case (work_base) DOES pass and exercises the
end-to-end contract; that's where the default-mode invariants are
verified.

External-consumer smoke
-----------------------

``test_external_consumer_can_load_bundle`` exercises the
self-describing-bundle contract: open ``manifest.json``, walk every
``exists=True`` file, compute a tiny summary stat (row count) per file.
This is the "fresh eye" gate from the handoff doc.
"""
from __future__ import annotations

